Upfield, manufacturers of the Blue Band margarine spread, on Friday unveiled their new range of products at the Tamambo Karen Blixen restaurant. Food enthusiasts and guests thronged the event, including celebrated Chef Ali and Pika Chakula who were the MCs. Guests were treated to a three-course meal that incorporated the innovations as part of the ingredients. The products launched include Blue Band Peanut Butter, an addition to the spread category. Upfield Africa head of corporate affairs and communications Omotola Oyebanjo was in attendance.